{
  "texts": [
    "Evidence based on internal structure evaluates how well the relationships between test items align with the proposed construct.",
    "An analysis should determine whether a hypothesized multidimensional construct is reflected in the test's internal structure.",
    "This is often done using factor analysis, which identifies the distinct factors the test is based on.",
    "Evidence based on relations to other variables can be provided by analyzing the relationship of test scores with external variables.",
    "This includes assessing the relationships to different tests that measure the same or associated constructs (convergent evidence) or relations to tests purportedly assessing different constructs (discriminant evidence)."
  ]
}